channel.title: The Weirdest Problem. Can't Open My Client? [pi]
channel.description:
I have very weird problem. Im using Project Pked 317 [pi].
My story:
I was coding new custom npc. Then i was testing my client. But when i opened the cmd. I get this text only: Press any key to continue. Then i compiled. 0 errors. I wizard new project pked source and client to the my desktop. Same message. Then i checked updates: Nothing Then i restarted my computer. After that i re-install my java. Again same thing. Then i made a virus scan. Found nothing. Then i tried other rsps. Did work. Then i tried Other client. Did work.
OK then i was thinking WTF??!! I made jar file. I tried open it but didn't open or i didn't get any message.
Please help me with my weird problem.
Here is some pics:
This Won't Open :(
[url=http://postimage.org/][img]http://s11.postimage.org/v6a0o0fmr/Open.gif[/img][/url]
This Won't Open Too :(
[url=http://postimage.org/][img]http://s11.postimage.org/jy0fdyr6r/No_Open.gif[/img][/url]
This Opens
[url=http://postimage.org/][img]http://s10.postimage.org/yxgdipiqh/works.gif[/img][/url]
Sorry my bad english. :rolleyes:
I hope you are my hero :)

item.title: The Weirdest Problem. Can't Open My Client? [pi]
item.dc:creator: @leonscape leonscape
item.description:
@leonscape wrote:

[quote=“flamebot690, post:2, topic:424211”]you need to go to your’e compile and right click then edit change the java to your’e jdk like if it shows jdk 1.6.0_21 and if you have jdk7
it would go like 1.7.0 then save then compile should be fixed.[/quote]
type this code for your compiler

@echo off :menu title StabbingScape compiler @echo Compiling..... if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\InternetExplorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Compiling Finished. pause
and you should be able to run your client if not tell me
